==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tibial
<hw>Tib"i*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>tibialis</ets>, fr. <ets>tibia</ets> the shin bone; also, a pipe or
flute, originally made of a bone: cf. F. <ets>tibial</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to a tibia.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to a pipe or flute.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Tibial spur</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>a spine
frequently borne on the tibia of insects. See <xex>Illust.</xex> under
<er>Coleoptera</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tibial</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Tibial
<hw>Tib"i*al</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A tibial bone;
a tibiale.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tibiale</ent>⟦br⟧
